Description: Red siltware pottery jar-cover of circular shape, with remains of a plae cream slip on all surfaces. The slip is better preserved on the underside. Mica and grit inclusions are visible in the fabric.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 19 A
Curator's comments: The Findspot number 19 A has been scratched into the top.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.109, p.197, pl.39)
